two main methods of building web apps:
	1) generate the page on the server and return the htl page the browser
	2) only return the data needed to build the page and let the browser do the work of building the page using javascript. this uproach is more scalable and is used in modern web apps.
		there are tools that are used to generate the page on the browser like react and angular and vue. these are called frontend frameworks.

django is a backend framework that can be used to build web apps using the first approach but it can also be used to build APIs that can be consumed by frontend frameworks using the second approach.
	the server becomes a data provider and the frontend framework becomes the consumer of that data and is responsible for building the page using that data. this is called a decoupled architecture.
	seerver = gateway to the data
		do we can provide different endpoint for different data 
		it becomes an interface fro the data
			API: like buttons (endpoints) of a remote (api)
				all the endpoint together represents the interface that we use to talk to server















